                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-14T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 14, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>88. War Department informed by message from Cairo dated October 12, with
                    reference to your 155, October 7, noon, to the effect that General Royce has no
                    plans for sending mission to Saudi Arabia but has merely made statement that if
                    Saudi Government wants Army help in preparing Lend-Lease programs an invitation
                    would receive favorable consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
